WEBVTT

00:02.114 --> 00:16.869
We talk about churches, we pray for churches, we're excited about church, we're grateful for Calvary Church, but we also have to acknowledge that a lot of us here this morning have suffered church hurt.

00:18.250 --> 00:29.682
What we mean by church hurt is those times when individuals in churches or even churches collectively have acted not in love and not with the spirit

00:30.114 --> 00:33.237
And as a result, we've been wounded by that.

00:33.678 --> 00:40.365
Many of us here this morning could tell stories of the hurts we've experienced at the hands of the church.

00:41.886 --> 00:43.588
It happens to congregants.

00:44.509 --> 00:46.051
Church hurt happens to staff.

00:47.072 --> 00:48.233
It happens to elders.

00:49.214 --> 00:50.956
It happens to people who are older.

00:51.897 --> 00:53.439
It happens to people who are younger.

00:54.240 --> 00:56.562
It can happen to people who are new to the faith.

00:56.834 --> 01:01.178
It can happen to people who have been around the faith for a long, long time.

01:03.661 --> 01:11.108
You said, last week we said that the whole world is under the control of the evil one, but the church is not.

01:12.609 --> 01:16.453
But that doesn't mean that Satan doesn't have any influence in the church.

01:17.735 --> 01:25.362
That there are opportunities where he comes in and whether it's an individual congregant or group of congregants being divisive and discouraging.

01:25.698 --> 01:32.449
Whether it's staff members or people in positions of leadership and authority being abusive or being deceptive.

01:32.469 --> 01:39.720
Whether it's his influence in the leadership in the elders or in the whole, can what can be toxic church culture.

01:40.201 --> 01:46.571
There are ways in which Satan gets in through our poor choices and causes hurts to happen.

01:48.173 --> 01:53.682
The hurts that happen through a church are especially painful because they feel like a betrayal.

01:54.722 --> 01:58.927
They feel like this is supposed to be the place where Satan is not.

01:59.729 --> 02:04.034
This is supposed to be the place where Jesus is Lord.

02:04.415 --> 02:09.541
When you are hurt by a church, it feels especially wounding.

02:11.444 --> 02:12.465
Like a great betrayal.

02:14.668 --> 02:21.597
The whole world is under the control of the evil one, but that is not supposed to be the case in the church.

02:21.617 --> 02:22.418
In fact,

02:22.722 --> 02:34.638
of the church, the one institution in all the world of which God Himself has said, the gates of hell will not prevail against it.

02:35.820 --> 02:42.088
Like in a world that is under the control of Satan, this is the place that Jesus is Lord.

02:44.512 --> 02:52.082
And so this morning in full acknowledgment that Satan has and does.

02:52.674 --> 03:15.007
use individual churches, people in churches to do great harm, that this is not God's plan for the church, that God has something different for us today, that he can, does, and will work through the church to be a light in our lives and in this dark world.

03:15.027 --> 03:22.578
And so this morning we have an opportunity to remind ourselves of what is God's plan for who we are.

03:23.138 --> 03:24.619
and what we're doing.

03:24.639 --> 03:29.164
Let me invite you to take a Bible and turn to the book of 2nd John.

03:29.184 --> 03:33.808
2nd John is a little letter all the way near the end of the Bible.

03:34.409 --> 03:38.172
It's page 989 in the church's Bibles.

03:38.212 --> 03:39.413
They're in the rack in front of you.

03:42.156 --> 03:45.239
2nd John is just 13 verses long.

03:46.880 --> 03:52.786
If you come this week and next week, you will have covered an entire book of the Bible.

03:53.602 --> 03:56.185
I get to preach half a book of the Bible today.

03:59.228 --> 04:06.957
Second John, page 989, we're going to look this morning at the first six verses, so the first half.

04:10.360 --> 04:22.834
John writes, the elder, to the lady chosen by God and to her children, whom I love in the truth, and not I only, but also all who know the truth,

04:23.522 --> 04:27.928
because of the truth which lives in us and will be with us forever.

04:29.530 --> 04:38.060
Grace, mercy, and peace from God the Father and from Jesus Christ the Father's Son will be with us in truth and love.

04:40.183 --> 04:48.053
It has given me great joy to find some of your children walking in the truth just as the Father commanded us.

04:49.014 --> 04:52.018
And now, dear lady, I am not writing you a new command,

04:52.578 --> 04:54.341
but one we have had from the beginning.

04:55.563 --> 05:02.373
I asked that we love one another, and this is love that we walk in obedience to His commands.

05:03.535 --> 05:09.324
As you have heard from the beginning, His command is that you walk in love.

05:10.606 --> 05:18.518
Now for the more discerning listeners out there, you might be wondering, I thought we were gonna be talking about the church.

05:19.299 --> 05:21.042
Isn't that what the whole introduction was about?

05:21.794 --> 05:23.256
This is a letter to some lady.

05:24.438 --> 05:28.304
Why are we talking about the church when this letter is written to a lady?

05:29.786 --> 05:38.219
Well, there are some people who think that the letter of 2 John is written to a specific female and her biological or adoptive children.

05:39.321 --> 05:42.125
I don't think that's what 2 John who that's written to.

05:42.706 --> 05:48.114
I think the lady being referred to here, this is a metaphor for the church.

05:48.738 --> 05:59.312
A local church, one just like Calvary Church, a gathering of people might have been large, might have been small, but this is a message from God to us today.

06:00.133 --> 06:13.029
Let me give you six reasons why the lady here is not a singular female woman, but instead the church and her children, which is us, those who are a part of the church.

06:13.069 --> 06:16.914
Six reasons why this is not a woman, but a church.

06:17.474 --> 06:19.137
Number one, she's unnamed.

06:20.699 --> 06:27.670
When we write letters in the Bible to people, Philemon, Titus, Timothy, when they're written to somebody, they get named.

06:28.471 --> 06:29.853
This lady doesn't have a name.

06:30.154 --> 06:32.177
She's just simply the lady.

06:33.759 --> 06:38.807
Second reason, look over at verse 13, the last verse of this little letter.

06:40.089 --> 06:45.938
John says, the children of your sister who is chosen by God send their greetings.

06:46.530 --> 06:58.125
It's far more likely that John is talking about a sister church that he's writing from than he is talking about this woman's biological sister and her nieces and nephews.

06:59.807 --> 07:06.555
Number three, John writes the letter and says it's from him as the elder.

07:07.717 --> 07:09.459
That's a church position.

07:10.280 --> 07:15.026
He's writing as the elder to a local church.

07:16.098 --> 07:22.226
Number four, look at the pronoun usage in verse five, for example.

07:22.367 --> 07:31.098
And now, dear lady, I'm not writing you a new command, but one we have had from the beginning, I ask that we love one another.

07:31.139 --> 07:37.968
He doesn't say I ask that you love one another as if this was a singular individual.

07:38.709 --> 07:42.514
He's saying we as the church, we should love one another.

07:43.618 --> 07:50.028
Number five, the second half of the letter, which we're not covering this week, but we will next week, talks about false teachers.

07:50.568 --> 07:54.795
And the idea we should not welcome false teachers into our house.

07:55.977 --> 08:05.411
It's far more likely that John means don't welcome false teachers into the church than that he's telling a specific woman, hey, don't have some false teachers over for dinner.

08:07.173 --> 08:12.882
And then number six, do you see the, and now verse five, dear lady,

08:15.618 --> 08:20.723
The word for lady in Greek, let's translate a lady, is the word korea.

08:23.086 --> 08:31.315
It's the feminine form of the masculine noun korias, which means Lord.

08:32.836 --> 08:38.683
Whenever Jesus is referred to as Lord in the New Testament, it's the word korias.

08:40.465 --> 08:45.490
Here, this word is korea, it's a feminine form of that.

08:46.434 --> 08:50.841
This is way too high a title for a particular female.

08:52.744 --> 09:10.834
What John is referencing here is this powerful point is that Jesus, who is Kuryas, is married to so to speak his bride, which is the church, which is Kurya, that collectively together we have Kuryas,

09:10.978 --> 09:25.213
and Korea, we have Jesus and his church, and what is being pictured is that you and I, who are part of this local church, in some ways we are the offspring of Jesus and his church.

09:26.975 --> 09:37.746
Now, if that sounds too Roman Catholic for some, look at this quote from John Calvin, who nobody has ever accused of being Roman Catholic.

09:39.874 --> 09:47.004
John Calvin says, no one can have God as his father who does not have the church as his mother.

09:48.486 --> 09:53.553
No one can have God as his father who does not have the church as his mother.

09:55.536 --> 09:57.759
You see as a side note to this sort of last point.

09:58.400 --> 10:03.407
There's lots of people in this world who are like, I like Jesus, but I'm not interested in the church.

10:04.668 --> 10:08.754
Or I'm good with Jesus, but I don't wanna hang out with church people.

10:12.034 --> 10:13.195
Jesus is not good with that.

10:15.177 --> 10:17.119
The church is his bride.

10:20.222 --> 10:24.166
We are the offspring of Jesus and the church.

10:24.787 --> 10:31.113
No one can have God as their father who does not have the church as his mother.

10:31.794 --> 10:37.800
And if you think that somehow Jesus is glad when we say, love you Jesus, hate your bride.

10:39.301 --> 10:40.242
We're mistaken.

10:41.346 --> 10:53.723
And the idea is that Jesus set it up this way that in order to engage with Him, we do it in connection with a local church like Calvary, like this church.

10:54.204 --> 10:57.208
This is what's so powerful about the way John is writing this.

10:57.628 --> 11:07.082
He says, I'm writing to the woman, the lady, the chorea, the church and her children.

11:07.102 --> 11:07.442
All right.

11:07.906 --> 11:08.927
Back to 2 John.

11:09.087 --> 11:11.250
This is a letter to the local church.

11:12.511 --> 11:14.313
What does God have to say to us?

11:15.654 --> 11:28.108
Verse 4, it has given me great joy to find some of your children walking in the truth just as the Father commanded us.

11:30.610 --> 11:37.618
Notice John says, some of your children.

11:38.626 --> 11:40.789
all of your children.

11:42.071 --> 11:44.935
We began the sermon by talking about church hurt.

11:45.996 --> 11:56.631
This is John's veiled way of acknowledging that, of his acknowledgement that there are some in the church who are not walking in the truth.

11:57.552 --> 12:04.402
Romans 7 talks about the fact that there are some in the church who are powerless against sin in their life.

12:05.090 --> 12:14.427
In 1 John 1, it talks about the fact that all of us are sinners, and that as a result, we all need to regularly be confessing to the Lord our sins.

12:14.687 --> 12:16.851
It's those sins that cause that hurt.

12:17.773 --> 12:24.185
Jesus tells a parable in Matthew 13 about the church, and He says in the parable, it's like a field.

12:24.245 --> 12:25.146
We're like a field.

12:25.627 --> 12:29.394
And in the field are growing wheat and weeds.

12:29.634 --> 12:32.177
And the weeds are incredibly destructive.

12:32.457 --> 12:38.944
And so the disciples in the story are like, hey, why don't we pull up all the weeds so they don't harm the plants?

12:39.885 --> 12:41.607
And Jesus says, not yet.

12:42.548 --> 12:49.596
And the implication is, is that while we're waiting for Jesus to return, that in all churches, there are going to be weeds.

12:50.718 --> 12:52.800
And those weeds cause harm.

12:54.782 --> 12:58.226
John is acknowledging, subtly, that not everybody

12:59.042 --> 13:02.906
in a local church is walking in the truth.

13:04.848 --> 13:11.454
As a result, we experience hurt and pain.

13:11.474 --> 13:14.717
We experience wounding and harm.

13:16.999 --> 13:22.144
But the thing I love about what John has done here is he's not focused on those who aren't walking in the truth.

13:23.746 --> 13:27.890
He's focused on the fact that there are some who are walking in the truth.

13:28.514 --> 13:34.783
that in every church where the Spirit is present, there will always be some who are walking in the truth.

13:35.364 --> 13:36.906
And this gives him great joy.

13:37.487 --> 13:39.830
Of course, we want everyone to be walking in the truth.

13:40.711 --> 13:44.477
But John is saying, look, there are some we can rejoice in that.

13:46.019 --> 13:48.242
The idea is that if you're in a relationship

13:48.866 --> 13:53.631
whether you're married to somebody or it's a friendship or a parent-child relationship or whatever it may be.

13:54.052 --> 14:02.641
If all you do is focus on the problems in that relationship, all the things that the other person has done wrong, you're not gonna have much of a relationship.

14:04.923 --> 14:08.607
If you do that with the church, you will find plenty of sinners in the church.

14:10.129 --> 14:12.251
You will find plenty of hurt in the church.

14:12.571 --> 14:14.994
And we are not in any way minimizing that.

14:16.898 --> 14:19.921
But John is showing us, there's also plenty of good in the church.

14:21.202 --> 14:25.106
There also are a lot of people who are trying to live out the truth.

14:26.948 --> 14:28.269
And that can cause us to rejoice.

14:29.110 --> 14:35.396
So what I want you to do this morning is just in your own mind, this is a quiet exercise that just you're gonna do, you're not gonna share this with anybody.

14:35.917 --> 14:39.160
Just for a minute, I want you to think of somebody else in this church.

14:39.200 --> 14:45.106
They could be in this service, they could be in a different service, they might be online, somebody that you know of connected with Calvary Church.

14:46.306 --> 14:50.192
It could be somebody you came with, but it'd be really great if you thought of somebody that you didn't come with.

14:52.155 --> 14:56.100
Can you think of anybody in this church that you think is walking in the truth?

14:57.563 --> 15:00.186
They're not perfect, but they're trying.

15:01.488 --> 15:04.553
You feel Jesus in them, they're trying to live this out.

15:04.593 --> 15:11.623
Can you in your own mind think of the name of somebody in this church that you're like, yeah, no, they're trying to walk in the truth.

15:12.244 --> 15:13.426
Take a second, think of somebody.

15:17.474 --> 15:18.015
You got a name?

15:20.679 --> 15:20.960
All right.

15:21.921 --> 15:24.325
Can you think of another person now?

15:24.345 --> 15:25.507
So set that name aside for me.

15:25.527 --> 15:26.568
Can you think of another person?

15:27.029 --> 15:28.231
You can look around if you need to.

15:29.112 --> 15:31.496
Can you think of another person that's walking in the truth?

15:36.084 --> 15:36.624
How about a third?

15:36.705 --> 15:37.846
Can you come up with a third person?

15:40.010 --> 15:42.674
Somebody you know connected to Calvary Church that you're like, you know what?

15:43.298 --> 15:49.630
That's a pretty godly man or that's a pretty godly woman or that's a pretty godly young person that's really they're trying to live out their face.

15:53.398 --> 15:58.688
Now if you can't think of anybody, I think that's probably a sign that maybe we want to get you more connected.

15:58.708 --> 15:59.690
There are a lot of people here.

16:01.012 --> 16:06.002
And so just an encouragement after the service and the sort of the crosswalk in the back, there'll be tables set up.

16:06.082 --> 16:09.606
Because if you're just sort of here and you're just coming up, there are, I can see them.

16:10.247 --> 16:13.111
There are a lot of people here that I know are walking with the truth.

16:13.131 --> 16:18.838
And if you don't know some of those people, we'd love to introduce you to them.

16:18.858 --> 16:25.947
But for those of you who could think of a name or three names, let me ask you this question.

16:25.967 --> 16:28.530
Aren't you glad to be going to church with such people?

16:29.890 --> 16:33.015
Aren't you grateful when you look around and go, you know what?

16:33.095 --> 16:41.829
The whole world's under the control of the evil one, but I get to go to church with him or with her or I get to know these people and they're trying.

16:42.129 --> 16:43.431
They're serious about prayer.

16:43.451 --> 16:44.753
They're trying to live this out.

16:44.974 --> 16:46.456
They're serious about God's word.

16:46.476 --> 16:47.778
They're trying to do what's right.

16:47.938 --> 16:49.140
They're sharing the gospel.

16:49.381 --> 16:51.905
Yeah, they're not perfect, but they're a godly person.

16:52.505 --> 16:55.410
That's what John is saying is, look, there are some

16:55.490 --> 17:00.137
who are children of the church who are walking in the truth and we should rejoice at that.

17:01.159 --> 17:12.256
What an amazing thing that in a world that is under the control of the evil one, that you can go anywhere and find some people walking in the truth.

17:14.019 --> 17:23.794
And the darker and darker our world gets the more and more grateful I am that on Sunday morning or Wednesday night or Monday night or Tuesday afternoon, I can come and be with you.

17:25.314 --> 17:28.998
and that there are people here, lots of them, hundreds of them, thousands of them.

17:31.080 --> 17:32.662
None of us perfect, but we're trying.

17:34.204 --> 17:36.566
And John was like, that's worth rejoicing.

17:39.890 --> 17:44.455
John has two things to say to us as the church, two commands in verses five and six.

17:46.757 --> 17:50.962
Verse five, first command, and now dear lady, I am not writing you a new command.

17:51.650 --> 17:55.754
But one we have had from the beginning, I ask that we love one another.

17:55.774 --> 17:59.618
This is a command from God to Calvary as a local church.

18:00.238 --> 18:05.704
And what he's saying to us as a church is what he wants from us is to love each other.

18:06.624 --> 18:10.588
There's a second command in verse six, it's related, but it's slightly different.

18:10.608 --> 18:12.670
So let me try to explain the difference.

18:13.591 --> 18:20.658
In verse five, John is saying that we should love each other in Calvary.

18:21.378 --> 18:23.981
meaning we should love other people at Calvary.

18:24.001 --> 18:31.929
We're gonna talk about loving others outside of Calvary in verse six, but verse five is us showing love to one another in this church.

18:33.330 --> 18:33.911
How do you do that?

18:34.111 --> 18:35.713
Well, there's a million different ways.

18:36.293 --> 18:40.578
Let me just give you a couple this morning that we can think through together.

18:40.598 --> 18:42.600
The first comes from first Peter 4a.

18:42.720 --> 18:48.626
In first Peter 4a, it says, above all, love each other deeply

18:49.410 --> 18:53.374
because love covers over a multitude of sins.

18:54.755 --> 18:56.677
We've talked about church hurt, which is very real.

18:57.758 --> 19:18.258
Let me just say that when someone sins against you in this church, when someone offends you, when someone says something to hurt your feelings, when someone excludes you from something that you should be invited to, when somebody does something that is harmful to you, when someone's selfish motives result in you being hurt, you have a couple of choices as to what to do.

19:19.842 --> 19:22.867
Your first choice is what Matthew 18 says.

19:23.928 --> 19:29.356
You can go to the person who sinned against you and you can tell them that they've sinned against you.

19:29.376 --> 19:30.899
That's a very valid option.

19:30.999 --> 19:32.140
It's a godly option.

19:32.241 --> 19:33.763
It's very much from the spirit.

19:34.544 --> 19:42.456
In that option, Jesus says, hey, look, if somebody hurts you in the church, which is sadly what Jesus says will happen.

19:43.137 --> 19:46.642
When that happens, you have the option to go to them and say,

19:46.722 --> 19:50.306
Hey, you've sinned against me, you harmed me, you did this thing to me.

19:51.308 --> 19:57.936
If they don't listen, you're supposed to take a couple of other people with you to say, hey, this is important, pay attention.

19:59.437 --> 20:06.907
If they don't listen to them, then you're supposed to turn it over to us, to the authorities in the church, the elders, and we're supposed to deal with.

20:07.347 --> 20:09.730
That is a very valid option.

20:10.971 --> 20:11.792
Can you put first Peter?

20:12.193 --> 20:13.394
Yeah, thanks, back up there.

20:14.255 --> 20:16.338
But there is a second option.

20:17.826 --> 20:19.227
And that's what 1 Peter's talking about.

20:19.948 --> 20:39.186
When someone sins against you, when someone harms you, when someone says something that they shouldn't have said, when someone treats you less well than you should be treated, when they exclude you, when they avoid you, when their greed or selfishness hurts you, 1 Peter 4 says, you have another option.

20:40.727 --> 20:43.090
You can simply let love cover over the sin.

20:44.851 --> 20:46.653
You can just simply be like, hey, you know what?

20:46.833 --> 20:47.794
I'm not perfect either.

20:49.410 --> 20:51.052
In your own heart, you can simply pray.

20:51.973 --> 20:53.215
And that's the God would forgive them.

20:54.857 --> 20:56.159
You can decide, you know what?

20:57.040 --> 20:58.743
I don't really want to make a big deal out of this.

20:59.484 --> 21:00.765
I'd like to try to live in peace.

21:01.827 --> 21:03.910
I'd like to let love cover a multitude of sins.

21:06.093 --> 21:12.682
Now, quick side note, it's the person who's harmed that chooses 1 Peter 4.8.

21:14.023 --> 21:15.986
If you're the person who did the harming,

21:16.514 --> 21:19.519
You don't get to say, hey, let's let love cover multitude of sins.

21:22.503 --> 21:26.089
But the reason why I'm saying this is Matthew 18 is absolutely valid.

21:26.209 --> 21:27.110
It's from the Lord.

21:27.250 --> 21:29.975
It's definitely useful and it's needed.

21:31.016 --> 21:34.121
John's gonna talk about false teachers in the second half of the letter.

21:34.141 --> 21:35.323
We do have to deal with sin.

21:36.685 --> 21:42.674
But if a church, all a church does is Matthew 18, if we spend all of our time litigating all of these cases,

21:43.298 --> 21:51.691
There's so much sin in the church and we spend all of our days sitting down with each individual who might have harmed us that doesn't make for a very healthy church.

21:52.973 --> 21:57.960
One of the ways we love one another is we let some stuff slide.

21:59.142 --> 22:00.124
And we think, you know what?

22:01.626 --> 22:04.370
They probably didn't mean that as meanly as it came across.

22:06.073 --> 22:06.513
You know what?

22:06.633 --> 22:08.757
They may have just forgotten to include me.

22:09.918 --> 22:10.580
Or you know what?

22:10.940 --> 22:12.242
What they meant for evil?

22:12.802 --> 22:14.084
God's going to use for good.

22:14.124 --> 22:16.307
I don't have to make a big deal out of this.

22:18.089 --> 22:24.297
So 1 Peter 4a is another way or is a way that we can show love to each other in the church.

22:24.317 --> 22:29.443
Sometimes Matthew 18 is absolutely the right thing to do and the spirit says that's what I want.

22:31.446 --> 22:38.615
Sometimes 1 Peter 4a is the right thing to do and the spirit says this is what I would like.

22:38.635 --> 22:40.818
A second way that we can love one another

22:42.082 --> 22:43.844
is what Sophie did for us this morning.

22:45.105 --> 22:45.866
She got baptized.

22:48.149 --> 22:55.177
Now lots of people, when it's time to get baptized, feel nervous about getting up in front of everybody.

22:55.417 --> 22:58.341
I mean, really the baptismal is hanging like 30 feet in the air.

23:00.043 --> 23:00.843
It can be scary.

23:00.863 --> 23:06.610
You look out and you see a whole bunch of people and you think, well, why can't I just kind of do this myself in my bathtub?

23:07.554 --> 23:13.004
or go out to Lake Michigan and while no one's looking, jump off the side of the boat into the water and be like, I'm good, I'm baptized.

23:16.129 --> 23:18.694
We do it this way out of love.

23:20.377 --> 23:21.839
You need to hear Sophie's testimony.

23:23.703 --> 23:26.067
We need to be, you were blessed by that, weren't you?

23:26.147 --> 23:26.548
I was.

23:27.650 --> 23:32.338
You listen to that and you think, man, I love Jesus more now because I see how Jesus treated her.

23:34.658 --> 23:37.402
And so we do this out of love for each other.

23:37.442 --> 23:41.388
And I know lots of you might be like, I'm kind of scared to this.

23:41.409 --> 23:46.176
Yeah, most people are, we get scared to get up in front of people and be vulnerable and to share our story.

23:46.516 --> 23:49.842
But we do it first out of love for God because he commanded it.

23:50.202 --> 23:59.497
But secondly, out of love for each other, this is a tangible way that we show love to each other is through the waters of baptism.

23:59.517 --> 24:02.962
So there are a million more examples, but these are just two.

24:03.842 --> 24:15.715
of what John is talking about when he says, look, if you want to be a church that is walking in the truth, if you want to be a church where love is reigning overall, then choose to love one another.

24:18.278 --> 24:22.002
Second command in verse six is related, but slightly different.

24:22.743 --> 24:32.914
This is love, verse six, that we walk in obedience to his commands, as you have heard from the beginning, his command is that you, meaning us, walk in love.

24:34.882 --> 24:45.822
To understand how verse 6 and verse 5 fit together, there's a parallel, slight parable, to what Jesus says when He tells us to love your neighbor as yourself.

24:47.284 --> 24:49.628
In that command, there's actually two parts.

24:50.510 --> 24:52.774
You love your neighbor as you love yourself.

24:52.794 --> 24:57.202
The implications, you do need to love yourself and love your neighbor.

24:57.858 --> 25:07.371
that if you have self-loathing, if you hate yourself, if you refuse to acknowledge that you are worthy of love, that makes it difficult to love your neighbor.

25:07.391 --> 25:11.797
Likewise in verse five, what John is saying is that we should love ourselves.

25:12.578 --> 25:20.168
We should love each other in the church so that we are equipped to love others outside of the church.

25:20.288 --> 25:21.810
Our neighbors, that's verse six.

25:22.210 --> 25:25.475
So verse five is about you and I loving each other in Calvary.

25:25.495 --> 25:30.322
Verse six is about we as Calvary loving others collectively.

25:31.544 --> 25:33.447
Verse five is love in the church.

25:34.348 --> 25:37.713
Verse six is love as the church.

25:39.155 --> 25:51.954
For example, during this season of Lent, we collectively as a church, and you're like, well, I didn't choose this, you're submitting to what we collectively as a church are doing,

25:52.834 --> 25:58.382
have chosen to dedicate this Lenten season to sharing Jesus with others.

25:59.504 --> 26:13.444
Of course, you can do it by yourself, but when we do it collectively over these next several weeks, this is an opportunity for us as a church to love the world in which we live, that the whole world's under the control of the evil one.

26:13.805 --> 26:15.007
They need Jesus.

26:15.748 --> 26:16.308
Well, guess what?

26:17.590 --> 26:18.171
We have him.

26:19.153 --> 26:20.114
We're his bride.

26:20.674 --> 26:22.056
And we pray for other people.

26:22.076 --> 26:27.201
That's why we've asked you, hey, look, just pick one or two or three or four people and pray for them by name.

26:28.002 --> 26:29.404
You might not be an evangelist.

26:29.444 --> 26:32.727
You might not feel comfortable just walking up to somebody and talking to them.

26:32.747 --> 26:37.613
You might not have the kind of personality where you want to just sit down with someone and say, hey, let me tell you about Jesus.

26:37.633 --> 26:38.273
That's okay.

26:40.196 --> 26:41.617
But can you just pray every day?

26:42.538 --> 26:45.181
Can you just pick one or two or three or four names?

26:45.782 --> 26:49.586
Can you pray that God might give an opportunity for you to be able to just

26:49.666 --> 26:53.211
mention Jesus, mention God, do something loving.

26:54.613 --> 26:56.376
We're doing this collectively as a church.

26:57.878 --> 27:01.083
At the end, we'll talk about the fact that you can sort of text in those names.

27:01.965 --> 27:12.080
We're gonna pray for those people with you because we're doing this collectively because 2nd John 6 says that we as a church collectively should do things together.

27:12.801 --> 27:13.943
So we're doing this during Lent.

27:15.064 --> 27:16.947
I also think about our Jerusalem Project.

27:16.967 --> 27:18.770
We talk about the Jerusalem Project here a lot.

27:19.362 --> 27:24.008
But back in September, we planted a church in Ada called Frontier Church.

27:25.169 --> 27:30.256
We did that because, maybe hard to believe, Ada is under the control of the evil one.

27:31.858 --> 27:37.525
And in order to fight back that darkness, God led us to plant another church in Ada.

27:37.565 --> 27:40.208
Now, a lot of the people that are there are friends of ours.

27:40.469 --> 27:43.813
They're people who we used to go to church with, who we don't get to see as much.

27:44.153 --> 27:48.018
The reason why we did this is because we want to love Ada.

27:49.090 --> 27:50.312
We want to love Grand Rapids.

27:50.832 --> 27:53.295
We want to see light and not darkness.

27:54.217 --> 27:55.618
We have residents here at Calvary.

27:55.638 --> 28:04.250
These are people that may not ever be on staff full-time at Calvary, but we're doing this out of love for the wider church and for the wider community.

28:04.330 --> 28:07.774
How do we train up people and then send them out to be a blessing?

28:09.897 --> 28:11.319
I think of the Jonathan Fund.

28:12.240 --> 28:16.946
The Jonathan Fund is one of the four ways we sort of do some extra giving at Calvary.

28:17.410 --> 28:20.535
And we focus on the Jonathan Fund during the season of Lent.

28:21.817 --> 28:30.290
What the Jonathan Fund is, as it comes from the Old Testament story of Jonathan and David, and Jonathan befriends David at a very difficult time in David's life.

28:30.671 --> 28:33.215
And he comes alongside of him and he helps him emotionally.

28:34.537 --> 28:35.839
Go through this difficult time.

28:36.220 --> 28:39.525
The Jonathan Fund is a fund that we administer here at Calvary Church.

28:39.565 --> 28:42.189
Now it is for people at Calvary, but we're doing it collectively.

28:43.451 --> 28:45.394
And it's not need-based

28:45.730 --> 28:47.272
It's emotion-based.

28:48.433 --> 29:02.750
If someone is going through a time of suffering, if they're just really in the middle of it, it's an opportunity for us as a church collectively to show love to that person to say, hey, we got this for you.

29:03.652 --> 29:04.793
We've arranged this for you.

29:04.813 --> 29:11.761
We're paying for this for you because we want you to know that you're seen and that you're loved and that you're not forgotten.

29:13.023 --> 29:15.666
I think about the prison ministry that we do at Calvary Church.

29:16.898 --> 29:20.522
Some of you may never have done ministry in a prison, but guess what?

29:20.802 --> 29:25.447
We have done ministry in a prison sharing the gospel with others.

29:25.507 --> 29:28.130
That's the power of doing things collectively.

29:30.893 --> 29:34.657
We're able to do more together than we can individually.

29:34.697 --> 29:36.659
I think about our disability ministry.

29:38.922 --> 29:42.866
If you have loved and cared for a person with a disability, that's a beautiful thing.

29:44.130 --> 29:50.139
But there's also something powerful when collectively, as a church, we provide respite care.

29:50.520 --> 29:52.242
We provide worship opportunities.

29:52.563 --> 29:58.212
We give opportunities for those with disabilities to be able to participate and contribute in part of this church.

29:58.232 --> 29:59.153
That's a beautiful thing.

29:59.213 --> 30:03.640
That's John, 2nd John, verse 6.

30:03.660 --> 30:05.102
What are we doing collectively?

30:06.524 --> 30:07.245
In a couple of weeks.

30:08.327 --> 30:10.290
Lord willing, there'll be somebody from the Middle East.

30:11.170 --> 30:20.999
who will be our speaker on that morning for Global Mission Sunday, and he'll tell us about amazing stuff God is doing in the Middle East, and that Calvary is a small part of that.

30:22.300 --> 30:41.138
You may know that a good portion of our resources as a church go to Global Missions to spreading the gospel around the world because we believe that if we're going to be light, the whole world's under the control of the evil one, it's our job to try to spread that light by loving those who may be culturally and ethnically different than us.

30:41.794 --> 30:44.217
And we do that around the world.

30:48.503 --> 30:55.032
We also love the city of Grand Rapids by renting out this facility for Christians and non-Christians to use.

30:56.213 --> 30:59.197
Now, we do have to charge a fee because there are costs associated with it.

31:00.259 --> 31:04.604
But one of the things is we don't ask groups to say, hey, look, will you sign on to our doctrinal statement?

31:04.624 --> 31:05.205
Do you believe ever?

31:05.706 --> 31:08.850
Lots of people who rent this facility don't even believe in Jesus at all.

31:09.634 --> 31:11.877
You're like, well, why let them use the building?

31:12.358 --> 31:14.461
Because this is a gift from God to us.

31:15.242 --> 31:18.728
And when we share this with others, we're sharing the love of Jesus with others.

31:19.809 --> 31:22.033
We want them to know, hey, look, this isn't a scary place.

31:22.053 --> 31:22.694
You can come here.

31:23.595 --> 31:26.539
And if you came here for a high school graduation, maybe you'd come here for church.

31:28.042 --> 31:31.908
This is a way that we as a church are collectively showing love.

31:33.069 --> 31:35.012
That's what John is talking about.

31:35.032 --> 31:38.157
Obviously, I could go on with more and more examples.

31:38.177 --> 31:38.898
But here's the point.

31:41.602 --> 31:43.204
Church hurt is a very real thing.

31:45.608 --> 31:46.890
Satan does get in the mix.

31:48.152 --> 32:07.000
And whether it's a toxic church culture, whether it's a particular individual, whether it's an abuse of power, whether it's some form of deception, divisiveness, discouragement, false teaching, it is true that many, many people have been harmed by the church.

32:10.485 --> 32:11.186
But John,

32:12.066 --> 32:18.336
is reminding us that there's also a lot of people in the church who are walking in love.

32:19.779 --> 32:35.104
There's also a lot of people who are walking in the truth, that there are local churches that John's writing to, that Jesus is writing to today in Grand Rapids, lots of them that are light and truth.

32:36.226 --> 32:38.450
And part of the reason why Satan

32:39.362 --> 32:49.232
is not free to do in this world and in this country anything he wants to do is because God is placing outposts of light everywhere.

32:51.475 --> 33:02.667
And the darkness cannot overcome the light because Jesus is building his church and the gates of hell cannot prevail against it.

33:03.988 --> 33:05.970
And the letter of 2 John is a reminder.

33:07.522 --> 33:22.898
that although the church does do some things that are painful, that if you focus only on the wrongs and the sins and the difficulties, you're gonna end up missing something really, really important.

33:24.860 --> 33:35.250
And the thing that's really, really important is that there is great cause for rejoicing, because some are walking in the truth.

33:36.322 --> 33:38.886
Some are choosing to love their neighbor.

33:39.787 --> 33:45.635
Some churches, most churches, are working to be lights in this community and around the world.

33:47.237 --> 33:51.824
And this little letter, tucked away at the end of the Bible, is a reminder.

33:53.626 --> 33:56.911
No one can have God as their father who does not have the churches their mother.

33:57.892 --> 34:00.716
And that Jesus has shown himself to be faithful.

34:02.118 --> 34:05.042
That even though Satan, sin,

34:05.122 --> 34:23.058
and this world seem infinitely powerful, that we can rejoice, that Jesus is building his church, that hell is not prevailing against it, and that when you look around, there is lots and lots to rejoice about.

